'''Ahmed Azmeel''' is a Maldivian film actor.
==Career== Azmeel made his film debut in [[Aishath Rishmy]]-directed ''[[Fanaa (2010 film)|Fanaa]]'' (2010) alongside Rishmy and Aminath Rasheedha.<ref name=fanaa>{{cite news|url=http://www.haveeru.com.mv/entertainment/3102 |title=Fanaa: Proof of Yaaraa’s immaturity |language=Dhivehi |work=Haveeru |last=Nafiz |first=Ali |date=15 July 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100718092407/http://www.haveeru.com.mv:80/?page=dates&date=2010-07-15 |deadurl=yes |archivedate=18 July 2010 |accessdate=18 July 2010 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Based on a novel published by Waheed titled ''Balgish'', he played the role of a gangster.<ref name=fanaa/> Upon release, the film received mixed to negative reviews from critics; Ali Naafiz from ''Haveeru Daily'' classified the film as the "worst Maldivian film released so far" during the year, criticing the performance of lead.<ref name=fanaa/> However, other critics found the performance of Azmeel to be "good for a starter".<ref name=fanaa/>
In 2016, Azmeel appeared in Hussain Munawwar's ''[[Neyngi Yaaru Vakivee]]'' alongside [[Aminath Rishfa]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sun.mv/70075 |title=Neyngi Yaaru Vakivee's First show full, Tickets available at four spots |language=Dhivehi |publisher=''Sun'' |date=26 February 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160606110604/https://sun.mv/70075 |archivedate=6 June 2016 |accessdate=6 June 2016}}</ref> Critics gave the film negative reviews and considered Azmeel's performance as Kamal, to be "boring" while criticising the character development.<ref name=NeyngiYaaruVakivee>{{cite news|url=https://avas.mv/14598 |title=The actual reason of "Neyngi Yaaru Vakivee" |language=Dhivehi |publisher=''Avas'' |author=Nadheem, Ahmed |date=6 April 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160606101756/https://avas.mv/14598 |archivedate=6 June 2016 |accessdate=6 June 2016}}</ref> Despite the negative reviews, the film did average business at the end of its run.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vaguthu.mv/evaguthu/entertainment/391632/ |title=Neyngi Yaaru Vakivee premiered to a positive response |language=Dhivehi |publisher=''Vaguthu'' |author=Jaishan, Ahmed |date=5 March 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160606110957/http://www.vaguthu.mv/evaguthu/entertainment/391632/ |archivedate=6 June 2016 |accessdate=6 June 2016}}</ref> His next release of the year was [[Ali Seezan]]-directed romantic film ''[[Vafaatheri Kehiveriya]]'' alongside [[Maleeha Waheed]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avas.mv/16116 |title="Vafaatheriya Kehiveriya" is almost complete: Seezan |language=Dhivehi |publisher=''Avas'' |author=Maahaa, Aishath|date=9 April 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160609121943/https://avas.mv/16116 |archivedate=9 June 2016 |accessdate=9 June 2016}}</ref> The film received a mixed to negative reception from critics.<ref name="vafaatheri kehiveriyaa">{{cite news|url=https://avas.mv/18132 |title="Vafaatheriya Kehiveriya" is not bad: Here is the reason behind its failure |language=Dhivehi |publisher=''Avas'' |author=Nadheem, Ahmed |date=5 June 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160606082514/https://avas.mv/18132 |archivedate=6 June 2016 |accessdate=6 June 2016}}</ref><ref name="vafaatheri kehiveriyaa"/> [[Yoosuf Shafeeu]]-directed ''[[Baiveriyaa]]'' (2016), a comedy film featuring an ensemble cast was his second release of the year.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/10286 |title=Last film of the year, "Baiveriyaa" releasing today |language=Dhivehi |work=Mihaaru |last=Adhushan |first=Ahmed |date=14 December 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180330145254/https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/10286 |deadurl=no |archivedate=30 March 2018 |accessdate=30 March 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The film revolves around an aspiring actress who flees from her family to pursue a career in the industry and the suspicions and confusions that arise.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/11095 |title=Two shows of "Baiveriya" screening at olympus this week |language=Dhivehi |work=Mihaaru |last=Adhushan |first=Ahmed |date=3 January 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180330143550/https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/11095 |deadurl=no |archivedate=30 March 2018 |accessdate=30 March 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Upon release the film was positively received by critics. Nazim Hassan of ''Avas'' applauded the comic timing of the characters and mentioned that Azmeel showed "improvements from his earlier work".<ref name=baiveriyaa>{{cite news|url=https://avas.mv/26970 |title=Baiveriyaa: A fun and entertaining film |language=Dhivehi |work=Avas |last=Hassan |first=Nazim |date=17 December 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180330145015/https://avas.mv/26970 |deadurl=no |archivedate=30 March 2018 |accessdate=30 March 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The film emerged as one of the highest grossing Maldivian films of the year.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avas.mv/26970 |title=What was the best film of last year? |language=Dhivehi |work=Mihaaru |last=Adhushan |first=Ahmed |date=2 January 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180330150107/https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/10813 |deadurl=no |archivedate=30 March 2018 |accessdate=30 March 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>
In 2018, Azmeel appeared in Mariyam Moosa's directorial debut romantic film ''[[Thiya Loaibaa Dhurah]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/27018 |title="Thiya Loaibaa Dhurah" might turn out to be a beautiful romantic film |language=Dhivehi |work=Mihaaru |last=Adhushan |first=Ahmed |date=23 November 2017 |accessdate=18 September 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The entire film was shot in Sri Lanka.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/33272 |title=A new teaser of "Thiya Loaibaa Dhurah" released |language=Dhivehi |work=Mihaaru |last=Adhushan |first=Ahmed |date=24 March 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180328101423/https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/33272 |deadurl=no |archivedate=18 September 2018 |accessdate=18 September 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> It was moderately received by critics; Aminath Lubaa reviewing from Sun praised the music and story of the film though she opined the performance from the actors including Azmeel, could have been better.<ref name=ThiyaLoaibaaDhurahReview>{{cite news|url=https://sun.mv/104553 |title="Thiya Loaibaa Dhurah" review; a film for lovers |language=Dhivehi |work=Sun |last=Luba |first=Aminath |date=21 April 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180918081157/https://archive.mv/dv/articles/6kdQ4 |deadurl=no |archivedate=18 September 2018 |accessdate=18 September 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> In May 2018, it was premiered in Sri Lanka, and played two housefull shows at [[Mount Lavinia Hotel|Mount Lavinia Cinema]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://raajje.mv/news/32308 |title=Two housefull shows of "Thiya Loaibaa Dhurah" showed in Lanka |language=Dhivehi |work=Raajje.mv |last=Waheed |first=Thahaarath Mohamed |date=11 May 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180918081949/https://raajje.mv/news/32308 |deadurl=no |archivedate=18 September 2018 |accessdate=18 September 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>
==Personal life== In May 2007, Azmeel married one of his co-stars [[Aishath Rishmy]]; with whom he shared screen space in many songs.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.haveeru.com.mv/dhivehi/entertainment/47345 |title=Rishmy and Azey getting married on thursday |publisher=''Haveeru Daily'' |author=Ahmed, Fazeena |language=Dhivehi |date=24 May 2007 |accessdate=8 October 2012 }}{{dead link|date=June 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The couple were divorced in 2013.
